# AGENTS.md Maintenance

After any structural change to the codebase, evaluate whether `AGENTS.md` needs updating.

## What triggers an update

- New or removed: page, component, composable, store, API service, route, or env var
- Changed domain flow (upload, notifications, financial)
- New dependency added to `package.json` that affects architecture
- Changed conventions (file naming, API patterns, styling)

## Rules

- Update `AGENTS.md` in the same commit as the structural change
- Keep the file under **200 lines** — if an addition would exceed this, compress or remove lower-value content
- The **Inventory** section (components, composables, stores, API services) must always reflect the current codebase
- The **Screens** table must list every route
- New API services must use `apiRequest` from `apiClient.ts` unless there is a documented reason not to
